---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '@/components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy, Meld"
  description="How Meld protects your health data. Read our full privacy policy."
>
  <Nav slot="nav" />

  <article class="legal section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <header class="legal-header">
        <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="h1">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="meta">
          <strong>Effective:</strong> April 11, 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp;
          <strong>Last updated:</strong> April 11, 2026
        </p>
      </header>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how Meld ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses,
        protects, and discloses information when you visit heymeld.com, join our waitlist,
        or use the Meld iOS app once it is available. Because Meld is a health product, we
        take privacy seriously and want to be specific about what we do.
      </p>

      <p>If any of this is unclear, email us at <a href="mailto:hello@heymeld.com">hello@heymeld.com</a>.</p>

      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        Meld is an independent product built by Brock Howard. Our company entity and
        contact details will be finalized before the app launches. For now, Meld is
        pre-launch and primarily operates a waitlist at heymeld.com.
      </p>

      <h2>2. What we collect</h2>
      <p>
        On this website (heymeld.com), we collect the email address you submit to join our
        waitlist, standard web analytics about the pages you visit, and cookies that make the
        site work.
      </p>
      <p>
        Inside the Meld iOS app, once it launches, we collect health data from sources you
        explicitly connect (Oura, Apple Health, Peloton, Garmin, and others over time). You
        control which sources are connected. We also collect health data you enter directly
        such as food photos, workout notes, goals, and preferences. We collect your email and
        authentication tokens for your account. We collect usage data about which features
        you use. We collect any support messages you send us.
      </p>
      <p>
        We never buy, scrape, or acquire your health data from outside sources. Every piece
        of health data we see comes from you or from a source you connected.
      </p>

      <h2>3. How we use your data</h2>
      <p>
        We use your data only to make Meld work for you. That means coaching you based on
        your own data, history, and goals. Connecting insights across sleep, nutrition,
        recovery, and training. Improving Meld through anonymized product analytics. Emailing
        you about your waitlist status, product updates, and support. Meeting legal
        obligations if required.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do not sell your data. We do not rent your data. We do not share your data with
        advertisers. We do not use your health data to train generic AI models.
      </p>

      <h2>4. How AI is used</h2>
      <p>
        Meld uses Anthropic's Claude to power the coaching experience. When you chat with
        the coach, your message and relevant health context are sent to Anthropic's API for
        processing. Anthropic acts as our sub-processor and does not retain this data to
        train their models. Anthropic's data handling is governed by their own commercial
        terms.
      </p>
      <p>
        We never send your name, email, or any identifier to Anthropic unless it is
        necessary to answer your message. We send only the minimum context needed to coach
        you well.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Where your data lives</h2>
      <p>
        Your data is encrypted in transit and at rest. It is stored in a PostgreSQL database
        hosted on Railway. Railway is our hosting sub-processor. Both Railway and our
        backend are located in the United States.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our sub-processors today are Anthropic for AI inference, Railway for hosting, Apple
        for in-app purchase processing and push notification delivery, and Cloudflare Pages
        for this marketing website. This list will evolve and we will update this page when
        it changes.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        You have the right to see what data we have about you, to export it in a
        machine-readable format, to delete all of it at any time, to revoke access to any
        data source inside the app, to unsubscribe from our emails, and to complain to us or
        to a data protection authority. Email
        <a href="mailto:hello@heymeld.com">hello@heymeld.com</a> for any of these.
      </p>
      <p>
        Residents of California, the European Union, the United Kingdom, and other regions
        may have additional rights under their local privacy laws. We honor all of them.
      </p>

      <h2>7. HIPAA</h2>
      <p>
        Meld is not a covered entity under HIPAA. We are not a healthcare provider, insurer,
        or clearinghouse. We are a consumer wellness app. HIPAA does not apply to most of our
        operations today.
      </p>
      <p>
        That said, we treat your health data with the same seriousness HIPAA would require.
        Encryption, access controls, audit logs, minimum necessary access. If we ever
        integrate with HIPAA-covered entities or sources, we will enter the appropriate
        Business Associate Agreements and update this policy.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Children</h2>
      <p>
        Meld is not for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from
        children under 13. If you think a child has given us data, email
        <a href="mailto:hello@heymeld.com">hello@heymeld.com</a> and we will delete it.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Analytics and tracking</h2>
      <p>
        heymeld.com does not use cookies. We do not set any first-party or third-party
        cookies for advertising, tracking, or personalization. We do not participate in
        cross-site tracking networks. We do not sell or share any analytics data.
      </p>
      <p>
        We use <a href="https://telemetrydeck.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">TelemetryDeck</a>
        for privacy-first analytics. TelemetryDeck is a cookieless analytics service based
        in Germany and operates under GDPR. Each visit is tagged with an anonymous hash
        that is generated on our server and cannot be reversed to identify you. We track
        page views, scroll depth, and which sections of the site people interact with.
        We never collect your name, email, IP address, or any personally identifiable
        information via analytics.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our hosting provider, Cloudflare, keeps standard network logs (request timestamps,
        general geographic region, user agent) for a limited time for security and
        operational purposes. These logs are governed by Cloudflare's own privacy policy.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you submit your email to the waitlist, that submission is stored separately
        from analytics and is only used to email you about Meld, see section 3.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We will update this page when we change anything material. We will email waitlist
        members for significant changes. You can always see when we last updated this by
        checking the Last Updated date at the top.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about privacy? Email
        <a href="mailto:hello@heymeld.com">hello@heymeld.com</a>. We reply within a few
        business days.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal {
    background: var(--bg-primary);
  }

  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-12);
  }

  .legal-header .h1 {
    margin-block: var(--sp-2) var(--sp-4);
  }

  .legal .meta {
    font-size: var(--fs-body-sm);
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
  }

  .legal .prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: var(--fw-regular);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: var(--sp-10);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .legal .prose p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: var(--fw-light);
    line-height: var(--lh-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
  }
</style>
